title: Let Them Theory - Friendships
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Applying "Let Them" to friendships transforms dynamics by removing resentment.

* '''Stop the "Fixer" Mentality''': Let friends make their own mistakes. Preserve the bond by being a friend, not a parent.
* '''Release Reciprocity (Scorekeeping)''': Let them put in the effort they are willing to give. This provides clarity on the true nature of the friendship.
* '''Handle FOMO''': Let them have a night without you. Their choices are not always a reflection of your worth.
* '''Let Them Be Wrong''': Stop wasting energy proving your character to those unwilling to see it.